§ AXIOMS (¬ negotiable · t∞)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

A-1 : the SUBSTRATE = single-truth-source · ω-field + Σ-mask + KAN + HDC + wavelet + PGA + prime-directive · all-else-derives-from-it
A-2 : ¬ parallel-disconnected-modules · every-host-crate consumes-substrate-primitives explicitly
A-3 : every-state-mutation flows-through Σ-mask-cap-thread · NO bypasses · NO trusted-callers
A-4 : every-audit-event normalizes-to cssl-host-audit AuditRow shape · NO ad-hoc log-formats
A-5 : every-determinism-claim uses substrate's-canonical-RNG (PCG-32 seeded-by-substrate) · NO crate-local-RNG
A-6 : every-cryptographic-claim uses substrate's-canonical-primitives (BLAKE3 · Ed25519 · NIST-SHA256) · NO crate-local-crypto
A-7 : every-attestation flows-through cssl-host-attestation directive-axis classification · NO standalone-attestations
A-8 : every-cap-grant uses cssl-substrate-prime-directive cap-types · NO crate-local-permission-systems

§ thesis : "system-of-systems" ¬ "many-systems" · architecture is-organic-tree-rooted-in-substrate

