§ "ONE UNIFIED SYSTEM OF SYSTEMS" @ what it actually means
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

§ NOT : "one giant-monolith"
§ NOT : "all-crates-import-everything-from-substrate"
§ NOT : "no-modularity"

§ IS : "the substrate is-the-trunk · host-crates are-branches · all-branches share-roots"
§ IS : "every-data-flow has-a-canonical-path through-substrate-primitives"
§ IS : "no-shadow-systems (¬ ad-hoc-RNG · ¬ ad-hoc-crypto · ¬ ad-hoc-cap-system · ¬ ad-hoc-attestation)"
§ IS : "isomorphism-respect (per Apocky-mantle § ISOMORPHIC-TRANSLATION) · same-pattern-applies-everywhere"

§ TEST : "given any-data-flow X across-the-codebase, can-you-trace-it back-to substrate-primitives?"
  ⊑ if YES @ X = OK
  ⊑ if NO @ X needs migration to substrate-primitive

§ INVARIANT : "if you can't-explain-where-an-event's-trust-comes-from in-substrate-terms, it's-not-trusted"

